W_a_I5E37N78Mzn86vvAeQ.text: Native New Yorker knows their wings!  I would only come here for the wings, and the wings are why I come here. You don't have to get full orders of one flavor, so I tend to mix and match.  I love the pineapple teriyaki and honey bbq, and the asian garlic ones are pretty good added in for interest.  I'm sure the spicy varieties are great, but unfortunately, I am a wimp.  The celery sticks are even good, none of that not-yet-ripe, inch-long, only-2-pieces business.  I haven't tried any of the other food... I haven't felt the need to do so yet.    There's a patio if the weather permits.  It has its own bar and some TVs, so it's nice if you're there for the sports.  Inside, there are more than enough TVs to scream at.  I shouldn't have written this review so early, I'm going to be daydreaming about chicken wings all day!

Pj1--9CafZ9TeCaAEju_xw.text: Welp, won't be coming back here again. I just moved here about a week and a half ago. This place is close by and has an outdoor patio. This is pretty standard (maybe with the exception of water) for almost all food establishments with patios. I was there for about an hour without incident when a man comes out that I found out afterwards is the owner. His name was Shawn/Sean/Shaun. My dog barks upon hearing his voice. Mind you, not one single other person is on the patio. Sheauwn asks me if it's a "service dog". My only response is that I clarified beforehand to see if it was ok to bring him in. Here's the funny thing; HE IS CERTIFIED. I just don't like to take advantage or flaunt it by any means. He goes inside, obviously to address such an egregious error on the bartenders part, comes back and gives me the, "it's ok right now line, but in the future, he has to be well behaved. Obviously, he's going to respond to anyone that walks in here the way he did to me." Not True, about 4 to 5 other people were there briefly and he didn't do that. Anyways, his entire tone was condescending and just plain ran me off. Their food isn't anything exceptional, by any means, and the only reason I've been back was because of the patio and a few interactions with nice employees. Also, I've been a bartender for 10 years and in the service industry for 20, I know power trips when I see them. This was just not a way to approach your customers and make them feel welcomed in your establishment. There are plenty of other actual dog friendly patios with better food and a warmer atmosphere within a mile of this place.

lIX0V0Lo0rUjAJZYEtsw-g.text: Used to be THE place for Buffalo style wings when they were "Native New Yorker". Now they've cleaned up, changed to Native Grill, and gone corporate. Gone are the days of nickel wings and $1 beers. Used to have just the classics: Buffalo mild, medium, hot - and 'suicide' for those wanting inferno heat. Now they have 20 flavors of spice from mild to extreme heat, sweet to BBQ to just plain spicy. Also, lots of other items on the menu like pasta, pizza...typical sports bar fare. Food and service is okay for that late dinner or mid-afternoon lunch. I wouldn't go out of my way like I used to, for NNY wings and beer. But will still come back out of nostalgia for extra crispy (well done) battered wings with traditional hot buffalo sauce. RIP, NNY! We miss ya!

Z9xKCz2Zv1nSiLyqyg9nuA.text: My daughter & went to this Native today for the wing special.  There was a wait when we walked in which I don't mind, busy day.  We sat & waited more than 10 minutes.
